&gt; I&#39;m currently using my HyperNEAT library with Boost 1.34 so I&#39;m sure
&gt; it&#39;s supported, as long as you made the appropriate changes to the
&gt; makefile (which you obviously did).
&gt; 
&gt; It sounds like the system can&#39;t find the boost library.  This is
&gt; either because you didn&#39;t install the boost library to a system path,
&gt; or because there isn&#39;t a copy of the library in the same directory as
&gt; the executable.
&gt; 
&gt; In linux, there&#39;s an environment variable called LD_LIBRARY_PATH which
&gt; you can set to find extra libraries.  It should work for OS/X too.
&gt; 
&gt; Here&#39;s something you can try:
&gt; 
&gt; 1) Copy the boost threading library to the directory of the HyperNEAT
&gt; executable.
&gt; 
&gt; 2) Run this:  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=&quot;./&quot; ./Hypercube_NEAT
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; P.S. If you dig up a better way to use the boost threading libraries
&gt; with cmake, please let me know.  Thanks!
